messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Who said...
messages.msgSnippet: ... Who said:   Justice is a knee in the gut from the floor on the chin at night sneaky with a knife brought up down on the magazine of a battleship
messages.messageBody:
>Quiz game.  Anyone recognize the quote?
>Throw some out for other to see if they can identify. <<<<

Who said:

 "Justice is a knee in the gut from the floor on the chin at night sneaky with a knife brought up down on the magazine of a battleship sandbagged underhanded in the dark without a word of warning. Garroting. That's what justice is when we've all got to be tough enough and rough enough to fight Billy Petrolle. From the hip. Get it?"

One of the VERY few things I have ever memorized willingly.

~Kelly

messages.subject: Who said...
messages.msgSnippet: E-mail is like  a prison. A prison with no walls, and no toilet. Quiz game.  Anyone recognize the quote? Throw some out for other to see if they can
messages.messageBody:
"E-mail is like a prison.
A prison with no walls, and no toilet."


Quiz game. Anyone recognize the quote?
Throw some out for other to see if they can identify.

Using google's fair, I guess.

Here's another one:

We might as well be dead. Do you think death could possibly be a boat?
(Spoken on a small ship.)

No, no, no...Death is.... not. Death isn't. You take my meaning?
Death is the ultimate negative. Not-being. You can't not-be on boats.

I've frequently not been on boats.

No, no, no- what you've been is not on boats.
